<div class="paragraph" style="display:block;"><em>Commending Amelia&rsquo;s World Series Champions<br /></em><br />Presenting to Manager Mark Borum a framed copy of House Joint Resolution 477 of 2023, Delegate Lee Ware joined Resolution patron Delegate Tommy Wright, right, in saluting the Amelia Dixie Youth Major League All-Star team, winners of the Dixie Youth Division Majors World Series of 2022.&nbsp; The presentation occurred during the March &rsquo;23 meeting of Amelia Board of Supervisors.&nbsp; Amelia&rsquo;s Dixie Youth Major All-Stars &ldquo;made history with an unprecedented 5-0 run in the tournament&rdquo; held in Anderson, South Carolina.&nbsp; Assisting Manager Borum were coaches Peter Dietz and Tead Harvie.&nbsp; Team members included Levi Borum, Carson Dietz, Evan Fisher, Taylor Harvie, Jordan Hathaway, Austin Miracle, Carson Roberts, Anthony Rude, Ben Schenck, Lucas Stocks, and Matthew Williams.&nbsp; Del. Wright, who has represented Amelia in the House of Delegates for many years, graciously included Del. Ware in the presentation as Delegate Ware expects to succeed him in the new 72nd House District taking effect in January 2024, after elections in November.<br /></div>
