<span class='imgPusher' style='float:right;height:0px'></span><span style='display: table;width:261px;position:relative;float:right;max-width:100%;;clear:right;margin-top:0px;*margin-top:0px'><a><img src="/uploads/1/2/7/2/127232404/published/img-2533001.jpg?1679665394" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 0px; border-width:0; max-width:100%" alt="Picture" class="galleryImageBorder wsite-image" /></a><span style="display: table-caption; caption-side: bottom; font-size: 90%; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: center;" class="wsite-caption">Del Lee Ware and John T Jackson III</span></span>
<div class="paragraph" style="display:block;">Assisting Delegate Lee Ware during the 2023 Session of General Assembly was young John T. Jackson III, who was one of two young people selected by the Speaker to serve as a Page in the House of Delegates.&nbsp; John is an 8th-grade student in Tomahawk Middle School and the son of Effie Robertson, of Midlothian.&nbsp; He carried despatches to and from Delegate Ware as one of 37 Pages&mdash;the other Page from the 65th District was Miss Sarah Kenney of Fluvanna.&nbsp; John is an outstanding student who enjoys Interact Club and playing chess, volleyball, and baseball.&nbsp; He intends to apply to be Senior Page during the 2024 Session.<br /></div>
