<div class="paragraph"><strong>The VEA Fund Recommends Lee Ware in the House 65th District Race <br /></strong><br />The VEA Fund for Children and Public Education has announced its recommendation of Lee Ware in the House 65th District race. &nbsp;The announcement was made on September 6.<br /><br />&ldquo;It is important that we lend our support to those who stand behind our public schools and the dedicated professionals who work in them,&rdquo; said VEA President Jim Livingston, who chairs the VEA Fund. &ldquo;Lee Ware stands up for children and will fight to increase our investment in schools, raise pay for teachers and other school employees, and &lsquo;Fund Our Future.&rsquo;&rdquo;<br /><br />The VEA Fund is supported solely by voluntary contributions from Virginia Education Association members and others. VEA does not contribute member dues-dollars to support candidates.<br /><br />A retired teacher himself, Delegate Ware represents the 65th House District consisting of Powhatan, western Chesterfield, western Goochland, and eastern Goochland counties.&nbsp; He serves as chairman of the House Finance Committee and is a ranking member of the all-important Rules Committee and of the Commerce &amp; Labor and Agriculture, Chesapeake, &amp; Natural Resources committees.<br /></div>

<div><div style="height: 30px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;"></div>
